soldiers call this 
recreation outpost panther paradise but it hardly lives up to its 
name 
some soldiers pass the time racing beetles or watching scorpions 
fight 
others try to run pass patterns on a more or less flat patch of 
sand that serves as a football field 
still others congregate at the px a metal shipping container 
or the cinema a tent with some cots and a television set showing 
marlon brando mumbling his way through the godfather 
four hundred yards away the m1 tanks of the 2nd battalion 
69th armor regiment known as the panthers lie in wait under 
camouflage netting ready to roar into action if the order comes 
paradise is ok but i wish it was a little farther to the 
rear said spec kristopher mccoy 20 from ft wayne ind 
the battalion clerk was among the two dozen troops who on 
thursday were enjoying a twoday break from the rigors of training 
but they were also waiting possibly for war with iraq 
the us military command is formulating a policy to allow 
troops rest and recreation outside saudi arabia last weekend the 
command opened its first fullfledged randr center in the country 
at a location off limits to everyone else 
in addition individual units have been ordered to set up rest 
centers close to their frontline positions this spot known by 
the soldiers as panther paradise is one of the first 
if it got any better than this i wouldnt know what to do 
said command sgt major tim gabel of forth worth texas watching 
brando from the doorway of the darkened movie tent where cool is 
only a relative term 
sgt 1st class richard hawk of atlanta who runs the operation 
said the portable showers and woodenfloored tents including the 
cinema are about as luxurious as it can get in the desert 
a trio of soldiers tossed a football around but they quit after 
a few minutes of trying to run pass patterns in the loose sand 
hawk said that in addition to watching beetles and scorpions 
the soldiers occupy themselves playing volleyball chess checkers 
darts and card games 
id like to have basketball too but this stuff aint too 
swift hawk said kicking the sand 
