<TEXT>
the new chairman of arianespace the european 
satellite launching company says it is time the spacefaring 
nations of the world have an equal footing in both their pricing 
policies and access to markets 
arianespace will not be able to continue its 10 years of 
successful growth if our competitors do not respect the same 
rules the same manner of behavior said charles bigot who took 
over as chairman and chief executive officer two months ago 
we are facing two kinds of competition he said at a news 
conference thursday we are facing competition against american 
launchers which are in the same kind of economy as ariane but 
we are facing also competition from soviet launchers chinese 
launchers which are coming from nonmarket countries 
in the competition with the united states bigot said 
arianespace hopes to get agreement to open the launch market to 
everyone the european firm he said has access to only onethird 
of the market since the united states will not allow military and 
government satellites to be launched overseas 
we consider our american competitors have access to all the 
market and we hope that in fact europe and the united states would 
get some agreement in order to open all the market to all the 
launch vehicle companies he said 
bigot said too he would like to see a change in the pricing 
policies of american launch firms 
there is a small but important difference between the 
launcher in the united states and the launcher ariane about fixed 
cost he said fixed cost is what you have to pay to maintain 
facilities and the tools for producing the launcher 
in the united states bigot said the governmental market pays 
for the fixed cost while commercial customers bear only the 
additional expenses for a given launch 
the way has to be different said bigot you have to 
divide all the fixed cost by the number of launches and you have to 
attribute to each launch the pro rata part of the expenses 
through american accounting the cost is lower and we insist 
to have the same kind of rules on both sides of the atlantic he 
said 
bigot said precautions must be taken with the competition from 
the soviet union and china which do not operate in a free market 
economy 
it is obvious they are not at all evaluating their cost in the 
same manner he said in fact they dont know exactly their 
cost because they are not the same accounting system 
arianespace proposes that europe and the united states work 
toward an agreement with those countries which would allow for an 
intermediate phase while they develop their economies during that 
phase they would be expected to selflimit their marketing 
activities bigot said 
after this period we could accept free access to the market 
when they demonstrate that they have adopted the same rules for the 
economy he said 
