<TEXT>
an antisemitic quote in an independent 
dartmouth college paper known for its strong criticisms of 
minorities has infuriated people on and off campus who say they 
wont stand for further such incidents 
but trustees and staffers of the dartmouth review insist a 
saboteur placed the adolf hitler quote in the publication and they 
have apologized they further claimed that university president 
james freedman and others have created a lynchmob mentality on 
campus 
about 2000 people attended a rally thursday to denounce the 
quote and the paper history professor bruce nelson told the crowd 
the review lacks a shred of intellectual integrity and that the 
quote is the latest example of the smallminded meanspirited 
scribblings of the local hate sheet 
freedman called the quote an egregious expression of 
antisemitism 
for the last 10 years these shameless voices have ranted that 
dartmouth is for some but not for others he said these voices 
have preached exclusion from the dartmouth family and have expected 
us to heed their words what kind of people did they think we 
were 
even congressmen have responded on thursday 84 representatives 
signed a letter from rep chet atkins dmass to freedman 
denouncing the quote 
recent inclusion of virulent antisemitic remarks has made the 
review worthy of condemnation by all those in this nation who are 
repulsed by wanton expressions of hatred injustice and cruelty 
the letter said 
staffers and trustees at the review say theyve suffered 
unjustly for an act by someone determined to discredit the paper 
trustee dinesh dsouza said students at the paper have received 
death threats and he strongly criticized freedman and others for 
not helping the paper find the perpetrator 
unfortunately dartmouth officials to date have shown no 
interest in uncovering what happened and indeed convened a 
lynchmob to make scapegoats of innocent students dsouza said 
in a total abdication of their leadership and responsibility 
college officials are manipulating the grave issue of antisemitism 
for ends of selfaggrandizement and expediency 
the review published since 1980 has been vilified through the 
years for its views on women homosexuals blacks and indians 
william cole a black music professor resigned in august after 
the review attacked him for seven years in print belittling him as 
a mediocre teacher cole said the attacks compromised his 
effectiveness 
review staffers also were involved in a 1986 sledgehammer attack 
on shanties erected on the campus green as part of a protest 
against segregation in south africa several staffers were 
suspended 
the latest edition of the review was distributed saturday on 
yom kippur the jewish day of atonement and judaisms most solemn 
day the quotation from hitlers mein kampf was inserted 
unattributed into the statement of principles on the reviews 
masthead 
therefore i believe today that i am acting in the sense of 
the almighty creator by warding off the jews i am fighting for 
the lords work 
backlash from the quote caused the reviews president and two 
staffers to quit earlier in the week 
the antisemitic quote was not the first time the paper has 
angered jews in 1988 the review ran a column likening freedman 
whos jewish to hitler and the effects of his campus policies to 
the holocaust 
dsouza said the 1988 column was sophomoric and in bad 
taste he said trustees apologized for it at the time 
dartmouth religion professor arthur hertzberg vice president of 
the world jewish congress called the latest controversy an act 
of hooliganism and attacked the reviews supporters including 
syndicated columnists patrick buchanan and william f buckley and 
the new yorkbased john m olin foundation 
my quarrel is with those who put up hundreds of thousands of 
dollars with which to contaminate this campus he said 
dsouza suggested the quote was surgically implanted he 
pointed to an apostrophe in the quote thats different from the 
type used by paper suggesting it was typed by someone unfamiliar 
with the paper or added by an outsider 
editor in chief kevin pritchett who also has taken over as 
president said he should have been more vigilant i will do 
everything in my power to find the person who did this 
pritchett said that if anything the paper is proisrael he 
also said editors dont check the papers masthead daily so it was 
easy to miss the quote which appeared within the context of the 
reviews normal credo a quote from theodore roosevelt 
