<TEXT>
a small earthquake centered 6 miles 
north of here jolted large numbers of residents awake but caused 
no injuries or damage authorities said 
the quake which struck at 1108 pm thursday measured 32 on 
the richter scale of ground motion said rick lester of the us 
geological survey 
we received lots of calls from people who said it woke them 
up said denise franklin a reporter with the santa cruz 
sentinel it was two sharp jolts and a boom sound 
authorities also received quite a few calls but no reports 
of injuries or destruction said a county sheriffs dispatcher who 
declined to give her name 
the northern california earthquake of oct 17 1989 measured 
71 on the richter scale and killed 67 people 
the scale measures the magnitude of a quake according to ground 
motion as recorded on seismographs every increase of one digit 
represents a tenfold increase of magnitude 
