<TEXT>
garbage truck drivers friday ended an 18day strike 
that produced huge piles of uncollected trash on paris sidewalks 
and forced emergency action by city officials 
union leaders said the strikers decided to return to work even 
though their wage demands were not fully met 
jean tibiri chief deputy to mayor jacques chirac said the city 
decided unilaterally to implement its offer to increase the 
drivers pay by 23 to 39 a month according to seniority 
tibiri said no reprisals would be taken against the 600 drivers 
who heeded the strike call of the leftist general confederation of 
labor but he said they would not be paid for the days they were on 
strike as the drivers had demanded 
on sept 21 the fourth day of the strike chirac announced 
private firms had been hired to collect the fastaccumulating 
trash he also took legal action that forced the strikers to 
abandon blockades at the three incineration plants where garbage 
from throughout the metropolitan region is taken 
chirac said the health of more than 4 million people was at 
risk 
</TEXT>
