have been envisioned by sir hugh beaver on nov 10 1951 the 
fateful day his hunting party missed a flock of golden plover 
seeking a reason for the failure beaver searched a reference 
book for proof that the golden plover was britains fastest game 
bird 
it isnt the 1991 guinness book of records lists the red grouse 
as britains fastest bird 
