managing director of guinness the beer brewer pictured unanswered 
questions arising in debates in pubs throughout britain 
the guinness book of records was born in 1974 it earned its 
own place in the record books as the topselling copyright book in 
publishing history with sales of 239 million copies 
in october global sales surpassed 65 million equivalent to 182 
stacks each as high as mount everest 
