<TEXT>
the military chief of the soviet union said 
friday that the most important thing in the persian gulf crisis 
is preventing it from escalating into a war 
i very much want everybody to attune their consciousness to 
the idea that youve got to find a political settlement and not be 
thinking about how best to use military force said gen mikhail 
a moiseyev chief of the soviet general staff 
president bush has not ruled out using the more than 
170000strong us sea air and land force in the gulf to try to 
dislodge the iraqi army from kuwait the washington post reported 
friday that bush has begun consulting with congress on the possible 
use of force 
moiseyev spoke at an unusual joint news conference at the 
pentagon with his american counterpart gen colin l powell 
chairman of the joint chiefs of staff 
powell accompanied moiseyev on a crosscountry tour of us 
military and civilian sites including a visit friday to north 
island naval air station near san diego and to the cheyenne 
mountain complex in colorado headquarters of the north american 
air defense command 
moiseyev said that after leaving washington on friday evening he 
would stop in havana for a meeting with the chief of the cuban 
general staff 
at the news conference moiseyev deflected questions about the 
likely soviet response to a usled attack on iraqi forces in 
kuwait he stressed several times that moscow saw enormous danger 
in any military conflict in the gulf 
the most important thing for all of us is to not allow a 
military conflict to develop out of this situation the general 
said through an interpreter we have not exhausted the whole of 
the arsenal of political possibilities that we have at our 
disposal he added referring to the nations against iraq 
moiseyev also stressed in response to questions about the 
presence of soviet military specialists in iraq that they are 
gradually withdrawing and that their role is relatively 
unimportant 
these are not advisers he said these are technicians 
the general said the 206 soviet military specialists in iraq 
include 42 interpreters 15 members of a management team and 146 
technical specialists he did not mention the function of the 
other three 
moiseyev spoke warmly of his weeklong visit to the united 
states his first in addition to seeing military installations and 
equipment moiseyev and his staff visited national memorials in 
washington an automobile plant in michigan and san francisco 
we discovered america for ourselves he said we got 
convinced that americans are determined to keep the peace 
cooperate and further strengthen normal ties with the soviet union 
much has changed in our perception of america 
powell and moiseyev signed an agreement on military exchanges 
for 1991 and 1992 including a visit by powell to the soviet union 
next summer and a visit to the united states early next year by the 
soviet commander in chief of far east forces 
