marcos 
ordinarily however the mutineers simply surrender after 
protracted negotiations key leaders of past revolts have 
disappeared ordinary soldiers are then sent to different units for 
retraining 
senior commanders appeared fearful that bloodshed would further 
divide the armed forces and encourage sympathy for brother 
soldiers within the ranks 
