148 million abroad in the first six months of the year an 
increase of more than 400 percent over the same time last year 
in an editorial friday the progovernment newspaper the manila 
chronicle warned that instability was sapping the nations viality 
the governments mistakes and shortcomings of the past 
have exhausted the nation the newspaper said though most 
people still look forward to the 1992 elections for some possible 
relief there are those who are becoming seduced by the idea of an 
earlier more radical change 
 
