a follower of the late guru bhagwan shree 
rajneesh was arrested in germany in a plot to kill the chief 
federal prosecutor in oregon authorities said friday 
carol matthews 40 a new york native also known as prem 
samadhi was arrested thursday by police in baden baden assistant 
us attorney baron c sheldahl said 
we are beginning the extradition process sheldahl said 
adding that it would be months before matthews could be returned to 
the united states 
matthews is one of three rajneeshees being held in germany in 
connection with an alleged wiretapping scheme and a conspiracy to 
kill us attorney charles h turner during 1985 and 1986 at 
rajneeshpuram the sects former commune in central oregon 
federal prosecutors said anand sheela who as the gurus 
secretary led the sect devised the murder plot because she 
believed it would derail state and federal investigations for 
immigration fraud and other offenses 
sheela left the united states in december 1988 after serving 29 
months in a california prison for crimes related to the sects 
activities in oregon 
they included the poisoning of 750 people by contaminating salad 
bars in the dalles with salmonella bacteria cultivated in the 
sects laboratory the operation of a wiretapping scheme that 
intercepted all telephone calls in rajneeshpuram and immigration 
fraud 
matthews is the fifth rajneeshee arrested within the past month 
in connection with the alleged plot catherine jane stubbs 45 a 
native of australia and richard kevin langford 40 a native of 
syracuse ny were arrested three weeks ago in west germany ann 
phyllis mccarthy 43 a german native was arrested in south 
africa british citizen susan lissanevitch 43 was arrested in 
england 
sheela has not yet been arrested in the plot although turner 
said recently that authorities have a pretty good idea of her 
whereabouts 
