nasa workers loaded rocket fuel on 
space shuttle discovery friday preparing the craft for a saturday 
morning launch of the spacecraft carrying the nuclearpowered solar 
probe ulysses 
pumping more than half a million gallons of liquid hydrogen and 
oxygen into the fuel tank was a critical test of the shuttles 
rocket plumbing system fuel leaks earlier caused four launch 
scrubs in discoverys sister ships but officials said no leaks 
were immediately found friday night 
discovery was scheduled to lift off at 735 am saturday 
