babies cost bucks that translates into 
big business for playskool a name once associated almost 
exclusively with toys 
today playskool sells everything from sleepwear to safety 
latches bibs to cribs its in a close race with fisher price as 
the leader in items for infants and toddlers 
the number of products under the playskool name has more than 
tripled since 1983 said bob stebenne president of playskool baby 
the division that deals with articles other than toys playskool 
baby will put more than 30 million products on the market this 
year he said 
playskool still makes a complete line of baby toys including 
raggedy ann dolls gumby lincoln logs and mr potato head 
its 1991 line will include a 33 collapsible baby carrier for 
parents on the go a 5 snack dispenser that resembles a bird 
feeder and a versatile clothing line that grows with the child 
through a system of fasteners 
we are honestly the most diversified company out there when it 
comes to what we do stebenne said though fisher price disputes 
that claim 
the change at playskool started about six years ago after toy 
maker hasbro inc based in pawtucket ri acquired playskool 
with its takeover of milton bradley by then hasbro already owned 
glenco infant items and its tommee tippee line 
we changed that whole product range from glenco to playskool 
because we knew we had a lot of equity in that playskool name 
stebenne said in a telephone interview from dallas where he was 
