many analysts who believe the nation is already in a recession 
government data to back up the theory is not yet available 
many analysts expected the labor departments report to probably 
show that the nations industries produced around 50000 new jobs 
last month excluding the lost jobs caused by the temporary census 
workers laid off by the government 
a jobs gain of 50000 would be considered mediocre especially 
when compared with the robust jobs gains of last year when the 
economy was producing nearly 200000 jobs a month 
before the recent rise in unemployment caused largely by the 
economys failure to produce many new jobs the jobless rate had 
