report broadly confirms many of my own conclusions 
fra must improve the training of its inspectors and it 
must use its data more scientifically in planning inspections and 
in assuring consistent application of safety regulations he 
said 
but carmichael also said that rail safety improved during the 
1980s he said his agencys success should be measured by overall 
safety performance from the railroads and not whether each 
instance of noncompliance is corrected 
