rising imports and overseas tourism helped slash 
japans trade and services surplus by 725 percent in august from 
the same month last year the finance ministry said friday 
despite some fluctuations the surplus in the current account 
the widest measure of a nations trade in goods and services has 
generally been declining in recent months 
that has been good news to japanese officials pressured by 
trading partners particularly the united states to cut the 
surplus 
augusts drop to 942 million from 343 billion in august 1989 
was the largest decline in the surplus since january when it 
