<DOCNO> AP901005-0215 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the securities and exchange commission wants 
the accounting profession to change methods 
whoa dont stop reading yet 
altering the way the beancounters count could mean big 
differences in the way a company reports its financial health that 
could have farreaching effects on your employer investments and 
future 
as we enter the decade of the 1990s we should consider a 
fundamental shift in the goal we set for the accounting standards 
for financial institutions sec chairman richard c breeden told 
the senate banking committee 
had such a change been undertaken years ago for example it may 
have helped avoid one of the worst financial debacles of all time 
the thrift industrys collapse estimated to cost american 
taxpayers 500 billion over the next 40 years 
how thrift assets were counted made all the difference said 
breeden using the currently approved method savings amp loans 
showed a healthy surplus in assets the cash securities and real 
estate they controlled 
but when the thrifts began failing and the government took them 
over and began selling off those assets the market value turned 
out to be a deficit largely because of the accounting for the debt 
securities which had made them grossly overvalued 
present accounting standards known as generally accepted 
accounting principles or gaap allow financial institutions to 
count debt securities one of two ways depending upon whether they 
were bought for trading purposes or for long term investment 
that treatment exalts psychology over economic worth 
breeden said in a recent interview i mean it comes down to an 
exercise for the regulators and accountants to try and determine 
what the motivation or intent was with respect to the holding of 
that security 
if the debt securities are being held for investment their 
value is listed as the purchase price or historic cost whereas if 
they were bought with imminent trading in mind they have to be 
listed at their true value on the market a practice known as 
marked to market 
in essence its like picking grapes leaving them in the sun 
and still calling them grapes long after theyve turned to raisins 
for example says breeden take a hypothetical financial 
institution that buys 1 billion in 30year treasury notes for 
investment 
the very next year they fell to 900 million the idea that 
for the next 29 years that loss can be carried as if it didnt 
happen it demonstrates the degree of distortion that can result 
from this distinction based on investment intent vs trading 
intent said breeden who as a white house aide helped draft the 
thrift bailout legislation 
breeden has made changing that distinction a top priority and 
has called in officials of the top accounting standardssetting 
groups to persuade them 
the sec oversees the accounting profession because accountants 
must certify the accuracy of financial statements that companies 
file with the agency 
but in the past the sec has left most of the rulemaking 
authority to private industry organizations 
the most important are the financial accounting standards board 
which sets the general rules for accounting gaap and the american 
institute of certified public accountants which oversees testing 
of certified public accountants and provides accounting principles 
for specialized industries such as financial institutions 
these groups tend to move cautiously when considering changes 
last month the accounting institutes standards committee withdrew 
a proposal that would have created tougher standards for financial 
institutions accounting methods but stopped short of a complete 
rollback after the sec complained 
at a meeting earlier this month with officials of the standards 
board and the accounting institute breeden urged them to 
reconsider guidelines for listing debt securities on financial 
institutions balance sheets 
weve committed to get back to chairman breeden within 30 days 
on whether or not we are willing to undertake tis project said 
thomas kelley vice president of the accounting institute said 
the accounting officials pledged to give breeden a response to his 
proposal in 30 days but kelley said the earliest such a change 
could take place would be the end of 1991 
theres no question something has to be done said walter 
primhoff director of professional programs for the new york state 
society of certified public accountants but he expressed worry 
over too much sec meddling 
the sec has not very often interfered in this process he 
said theres only been a few times where theyve come in and 
said we dont like what you did with the rule were going to 
change it 
if it happens occasionally it just shows there is a 
responsible public oversight but if it becomes a very frequent 
occurence accounting standards will become politicized and if 
they do the people who rely on them for making decisions probably 
will be forced to rely on them less 
eventually the sec may push beyond the limited issue of debt 
securities at financial institutions 
but even breeden concedes moving beyond that to other types of 
assets is a direction that we think ought to be pursued but that 
has to be done very carefully and very deliberately 
one of the other four sec commissioners philip r lochner jr 
said the commission has taken no action yet to explore a wider use 
of market price accounting 
its kind of premature to go beyond that we may go much 
farther but im just speaking for myself said lochner 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

